      <description>{% raw %} I wouldn&#39;t want to be a Sony sysadmin right now. F-Secure just blogged about evidence of a fourth hack at the electronics giant. This one is relatively harmless - a phishing scam being run from Sony servers - but this pattern of security problems should tell us a few things about Sony&#39;s SysAdmin staff:
1) They&#39;re powerless in their own organization.
2) They don&#39;t get to set IT resource policy.</description>
